seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b2"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>262 n.3</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>25</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [56d] ... by force [56b] ... (energy). They do not carry the burden here ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>218</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>153</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>22</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1979b"/><citedRange>32</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[57d] Six ... The imaginations do (not) let [anyone] hesitate here. ... With whoever he lay ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>218</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:siegandsiegling1983"/><citedRange>214</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">the beings [58d] ... perceive the one hundred kleśas! [In] pain he lives, who (by the kleśas) ... in two ways ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>251</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... [59d] Again at another time the Omniscient [was staying] in Rājagṛha on the Gṛdhrakūta ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:carling2000"/><citedRange>151</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:krause1952"/><citedRange>35</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1983"/><citedRange>10</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Just after having gone from the good monkhood into his house. [60d] Having left the discipline, having dismissed monkhood entirely ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b7"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>161</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>105</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>111</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... He saw the Ānanda [and] was slightly ashamed of it. [61d] [This one] returned from the almsround [and] (reported) the whole matter to the Omniscient ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b8"><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:hackstein1995"/><citedRange>174</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:schmidtkt1974"/><citedRange>446</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1954"/><citedRange>723</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1957"/><citedRange>179</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1972"/><citedRange>462</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1997"/><citedRange>117</citedRange></bibl></seg><seg><seg type="prim_transl">... Even earlier this one could not obey [the rules of] monkhood properly. [62d] He did not conduct himself according to the rules [and] did not [act] the good way and manner ...</seg></seg></choice></p>
