               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;h3&gt;General remarks&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The leaf includes the strophes 48-63b in a 4x13-syllable-metre (rhythm: 5/5/3 and 5/4/4) and deals with monks that gave up monkhood and returned to their civic lives. Due to the incompleteness of the text the translation frequently remains uncertain.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Most probably somehow belongs with THT 44.c, which contains no more than 4 lines and must be a part from the right side of the leaf, although the allocation is not beyond doubt. It is impossible to determine any specific Varga this text could belong to.&lt;/p&gt;</item>
